Iavan Pijoos, News24 (File, EMPD) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Pretoria - A 51-year-old man was arrested by the Pretoria K9 Unit after he was found in possession of commercial explosives and detonators in Pretoria on Thursday, police said.The man was found in possession of 30 boosters and 29 detonators, Captain Augustinah Selepe said.Selepe said explosives such as these have been known to be used in illegal mining operations and in ATM bombings.The suspect has been charged with being in possession of commercial explosives and will appear in the Pretoria Magistrate's Court soon.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.